                      <td valign="top" height="100%"><font face="arial" size="2" color="#FFFFFF"><span class="spnMessageText" id="msg"> <br />It's not so much about how hard the game is, but how hard it is ~relative~ to others (other classes) which play. You'll find that your fun in EQ is proportional to how well you (and your class) stack-up to others in the game. <br /><br />If you doubt this, go to Sol-A at level 65....you will have all the power in the universe! Goblins? Froglok guards?....what's the difference. It's all about how you compare to other players. There are WAY better games for people who get satisfaction from soloing (Might n' Magic etc.) or solve puzzles (Myst or whatever). It's how you conflict, cooperate and compare with other players that makes EQ fun.<br /><br />Sony cannot keep it interesting unless your class is on-average comperable to ALL the other classes. In fairness, that must be a daunting task.<br /><br />I feel pretty tough when soloing, my 2000 damage megaDOTs eating slowly away at even the toughest critters. But I must say, I feel pretty goofy when a WIZ crits for over 6000 hps, and I know it's going to take me over a minute to do as much damage, using 3 or 4 differnt spells as he's done in 7? seconds.<br /><br /><br /><br />-Morloc</span id="msg"></font><br><br></td>
