int was that the "fun factor" does NOT appear to play into the decision-making process for this game AT ALL.  (sorry I thought I had made that point fairly obvious in my post).  I'm talking about things like the frog guards in the new Grobb.  For a few days they were killable.  Now, being that they were a challenge (there's that word!) to split up, a challenge (again!) to kill, gave fairly poor xp, had pretty much zero loot (a 2pp shield?), and served NO purpose that would cause other players to be upset that someone was in there killing them, why were they made basically unkillable?  Because "players killing our new Froggie guards wasn't part of the plan!" That's why.  And THAT was my point.  I'm pretty sure everyone else got that, but then again not everyone skims over a post for the sole purpose of <i>trying</i> to grasp the main idea so they can flame the poster.  <br /><br />Who was it that said "reading comprehension is your friend"?<br /><br />PS - I see you have a character on Rallos.  Clueless thick-skulled person that I am, I should be easy pickin's for you.  Look me up <img src="images/batman_125.gif" border="0" alt="" title="" align="middle" /><br /><br /><br /><br /><br /><br />Sage Drexyll Dz'Deign<br /> Warlock, Farmer, Zekite(tm)<br /><img src="http://www.onethirtyeight.com/graphics-2/cg.gif" border="0"><br />Mortiferus Nex Necris...Ex Nihilo<br /></span id="msg"></font><br><br></td>
